# ESI Triage Classification Models

## Objective
Classify patients into 5 ESI levels using presentation-time vital signs from the PhysioNet 2019 Sepsis dataset, across **11 models** including a stacking ensemble.

## Proxy ESI Labeling
MEWS + Shock Index + O2Sat thresholds map vitals → ESI 1–5. See [data_loader.py](file:///Users/sreehariniganishkaa/triagemodel/data_loader.py) for full heuristic.

## Dataset Information
- **Total Valid Patients Extracted**: 40,336
- **Training Set Allocation**: 32,268 records
- **Testing Set Allocation**: 8,068 records
- **Feature Set**: HR, O2Sat, Temp, SBP, MAP, DBP, Resp, EtCO2
- **Processing**: 80/20 stratified split, median imputation, standard scaling

